&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;USB Programs&lt;/code&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;code&gt;Enable Optware&lt;/code&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;code&gt;Entware&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;Extensions&lt;/code&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;code&gt;force opt install&lt;/code&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;code&gt;Install to USB drive&lt;/code&gt;&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Run &lt;code&gt;df -h&lt;/code&gt;. If /opt was not mounted to USB drive, run &lt;code&gt;mount \dev\sda1 \opt&lt;/code&gt; to mount manually. Here &lt;code&gt;\dev\sda1&lt;/code&gt; is my USB drive. It might be different, just change the directory accordingly.&lt;br&gt; It&amp;apos;s gonna take a while to install the opt. A cuppa is highly recommended.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Make a swap&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;The memory of NEWIFI-MINI is only 64MB, SQL service will not run properly on it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;figure class=&#34;highlight shell hljs&#34;&gt;&lt;table&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;gutter&#34;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;code&#34;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;dd if=/dev/zero of=/opt/swap bs=1M count=1024 # might be a little more than needed&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;mkswap /opt/swap&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;swapon /opt/swap&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;Swap will not mount itself after rebooting. Add &lt;code&gt;swapon /opt/swap&lt;/code&gt; to the scripts to run after booting to mount the swap file automatically.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;Web Environment&lt;/code&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;code&gt;Enable nginx+mysql+php&lt;/code&gt;&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;Here I ran into 2 problems: No nginx, No mysqld. The solution is simple as well. run the commends below.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;figure class=&#34;highlight shell hljs&#34;&gt;&lt;table&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;gutter&#34;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;code&#34;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;opkg update&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;opkg install nginx&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;opkg install mysql-server&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Everything will be fine now.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; It takes a while, too. Wait until the information appearing in the log area.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Can&amp;apos;t download phpmyadmin. Take a glimpse at the log area to comfirm the version, and download the zip manually on laptop, then transport it into the router with SSH.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;mysql rebooting continuously. Try running mysql in ssh terminal. It says there might be some database missing. Change directory to  &lt;code&gt;/opt/bin&lt;/code&gt; and run &lt;code&gt;mysql_install_db&lt;/code&gt;. This will re-initialize the mysql database, and everything will be fine.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;phpmyadmin might fail. Try replacing &lt;code&gt;$cfg[&amp;apos;Servers&amp;apos;][$i][&amp;apos;host&amp;apos;] = &amp;apos;localhost&amp;apos;;&lt;/code&gt; with &lt;code&gt;$cfg[&amp;apos;Servers&amp;apos;][$i][&amp;apos;host&amp;apos;] = &amp;apos;127.0.0.1&amp;apos;;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#what-it-looks-like&#34; class=&#34;header-anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span id=&#34;what-it-looks-like&#34;&gt;What it looks like&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;/img/Lychee.gif&#34; alt=&#34;web view&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Due to the gif recording method, the gif can&amp;apos;t display everything in detail. The pictures look exactly as they should be in reality.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This is just a post to take some notes.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

